         <text>iCertis Contract Intelligence</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-4CB65913-7C0F-433E-932B-A2F44B57ECFE" signavio:alignment="left">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioDictionaryLink propertyId="name">
               <signavio:dictionaryLink>/glossary/379d0e2ec2f943cab5c10dc3521829f3</signavio:dictionaryLink>
            </signavio:signavioDictionaryLink>
            <signavio:signavioType dataObjectType="IT-System"/>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bgcolor" metaValue="#e1e1e1"/>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>SAP Ariba</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-53387C42-7D8E-43A1-BA76-DDB7EE3F3B4E" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>WS# is entered manually by CM and auto-validated in Icertis from Ariba</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-27BC8847-46B3-4EF9-9CD7-4044986C020C" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Review any information regarding the contract/quotation that may not be clear. Communicate specific needs (i.e. price, delivery time, etc.) that are not being satisfactorily met per the supplier’s quotation. Reach agreement on all outstanding issues with suppliers. Input from Legal may be required.  Details of information to review, include: terms of sale, duration, description/scope, service level commitments, quality level - payment of union fees, agency fees and crown dues (if applicable),mailing &amp; official notification addresses, identities of key contacts, etc. The strategy for negotiation should not be the same with major suppliers and secondary (part of the contengency plan) suppliers.   
has context menu</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-B6B9D656-37BF-40F4-B6C4-50B731AD71A2" signavio:alignment="left">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioDictionaryLink propertyId="name">
               <signavio:dictionaryLink>/glossary/f950a98ad5364a5bb3b03af902b76047</signavio:dictionaryLink>
            </signavio:signavioDictionaryLink>
            <signavio:signavioType dataObjectType="IT-System"/>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bgcolor" metaValue="#e1e1e1"/>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bottom="false" left="false" ref="text_name" right="false" top="true" valign="bottom" x="31.0" y="-9.0"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>iCertis Contract Intelligence</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-5142449E-CE8F-4199-A6C9-1C1383926255" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Process Tower: Procure To Pay
Process Group: Procure Materials and Services (Direct &amp; Indirect)
Process: PM-090-020 Negotiate Terms and Conditions With Supplier
</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-79E7A54F-4199-4E8A-907E-DEADCB93554E" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="#ff0000" fontFamily="" fontSize="" italic="" ref="text-left"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="#ff0000" fontFamily="" fontSize="" italic="" ref="text-right"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Flow has been migrated to BIC. Please inform the process steward Nageswaran, Rohan &lt;rohan.nageswaran@intel.com&gt; and BPM Champions D'Elia, Traci &lt;traci.delia@intel.com&gt;,Newman, Jennifer &lt;jennifer.newman@intel.com&gt;of any design changes that occur within the flow moving forward. This will enable us to reflect those changes in the BIC and WIKI business process documentation.</text>
      </textAnnotation>
   </process>
